📸 How to enter:

1. Visit Universal Studios Singapore Halloween Horror Nights on 10 or 11 October and snap your spookiest photo at the Under the Castle haunted house photo backdrop!

2. Follow @UniversalStudiosSingapore and @teamwangdesign.

3. Post your most creative shot on your public IG feed, tag us, and use the hashtag #HHN12UnderTheCastle

4. In your caption, tell us why you want to party with Jackson Wang!
 
5 lucky winners will get 1 invitation each to a private party with Jackson Wang at @AdventureCoveWaterparkSG on the 13 Oct!

Contest ends on 11th Oct at 11:59 PM. Winners will be contacted via Instagram DM on 12 Oct.

There’s no turning back once you’ve been pulled down ‘Under The Castle’. 
 
In the first collaboration of its kind, Resorts World Sentosa has partnered with TEAM WANG design – the luxury streetwear label founded by pop star Jackson Wang. Step into the gates at Universal Studios Singapore Halloween Horror Nights 12. 
 
Tickets are now on sale here: www.rwsentosa.com/hhn12

Make your OOTD look instantly cool with this easy photography tip.

Follow these steps:
- Shoot using the LIVE mode on your handphone camera 
- Go to gallery and tap into your photo
- Choose 'Long Exposure' instead of 'LIVE'

Viola! The people moving in the background will be blurred out.

comments: [('kuncoromeyvita', 'In universal studio singapore?'), ('kuncoromeyvita', 'Is there Mario bross rides'), ('xuan.cyxuan', 'Joined! 🥰❤️ thanks for hosting this super fun giveaway and hope to win the lovely merch for my nephew who loves the movie a lot too!!! #teamyoshi FTW!!🙌🙌 @universalstudiossingapore lots more fun times soon when the new attractions open!!!❤️'), ('itz_munmuni_revived', 'Have a similar experience as @hellomslinzx , even with the express pass we couldn’t get to all of the rides and the wait time was almost 100 mins in most of the rides , we could find our lost photos from the Shrek meet and greet and the Universal studio app for photo retrieval is not working at all to put a request through . We submitted our feedback’s but never received the emails to collect the goodie bags . Also the tax refund from the store remains unclaimed . The opening hours and the turnaround time is something you have to work on ! @universalstudiossingapore'), ('hellomslinzx', 'Hi universal studios, we just got back from USS and we had a blazin time. However, I would like to express my disappointment on behalf of my 2 little kids. It was a very hot day and we showed up early to be in line hoping to beat the queues. My kids were super excited. However each ride was around 45-80 mins queue time (we did not purchase express cards). I tried my best to rush them from one ride to another but as you know we need to pause, eat, hydrate plus that very hot day took a toll on my kids. However the message that I want to convey is - can you extend your park hours ? We did not have time to go on most of the rides and it’s really disappointing that the park is only open for 7 hours. Most big parks are open for 10-12 hours. With the short opening hours , it did not give us much time to take a break, dine properly nor shop for any merchandise at your park. I really hope you consider to extend or review your operating hours so as not to disappoint your visitors. Just a message from a normal mom !')]
